Executive Summary
Laptop II experienced recurring Windows Update failures, servicing stack inconsistencies, system instability, and loss of advanced audio enhancements.
A full clean Windows 11 reinstallation and controlled driver reconfiguration were performed to restore:
	• System stability and operational reliability
	• Windows servicing stack integrity
	• Full hardware and software functionality
A secondary non-critical issue involved the loss of a bundled game subscription entitlement due to OEM binding, which does not affect system security or operation.
